sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant TS as Tweet Service
    participant DB as Tweets Store
    participant FO as Fan-out Service
    participant TL as Timeline Cache
    participant Feed as Timeline Service
    participant Rank as Ranker

    Note over U,Rank: WRITE PATH (post tweet + hybrid fan-out)
    U->>TS: POST /tweet
    TS->>DB: persist tweet (Snowflake id, partition by author)
    DB-->>TS: tweet_id
    TS-)FO: enqueue fan-out
    TS-)Feed: emit to search + trending pipelines
    TS-->>U: 200 {tweet_id}
    alt author followers < 10k (push)
        FO->>FO: load follower list
        loop each follower (smeared on mass-follow events)
            FO->>TL: ZADD home_timeline (score=tweet_id, cap 800)
        end
    else celebrity (>= 10k followers)
        Note over FO: skip push, mark celebrity tweet for pull-on-read
    end

    Note over U,Rank: READ PATH (home timeline merge)
    U->>Feed: GET /timeline/home?cursor
    Feed->>TL: read pre-built timeline (push)
    TL-->>Feed: tweet_ids
    Feed->>DB: pull recent tweets from followed celebrities
    DB-->>Feed: celeb tweets
    Feed->>Rank: ML-rank merged candidates
    Rank-->>Feed: top ~50
    Feed->>DB: hydrate tweet bodies + entities
    DB-->>Feed: enriched tweets
    Feed-->>U: paginated home timeline
